# {{HOME}}/ — pipeline directory

This directory is the **GitOS agent system** for {{PROJECT_NAME}}. It is maintained
by the `gitos` skill (`~/.claude/skills/gitos/`) and is git-tracked alongside
the source code — it is an audit trail and long-term memory, not a temp directory.

---

## What is this?

The GitOS skill gives every repo a lightweight operating system: three agent roles
(inception, orchestrator, diagnostic), a work-order ledger, and a self-contained knowledge
brain. Humans open the repo and read this README; agents open `HANDOFF.md` and `INDEX.md`
first, then query the brain.

For the full role documentation see `~/.claude/skills/gitos/references/roles/`.

---

## Work side (human-facing)

```
{{HOME}}/
├── README.md              This file
├── HANDOFF.md             Birth certificate — project identity, lifecycle, acceptance criteria.
│                          Written once at inception; immutable after that.
├── INDEX.md               Work-order ledger — open / resolved / disproved / next-steps.
│                          The single task surface for this repo.
├── log_vocabulary.md      Catalog of all known log and output families (for diagnostics).
├── work-orders/           One file per work-order: WO-NNN-slug.md
│   └── resolved/          Closed work-orders moved here when fixed and verified.
├── roles/
│   ├── inception.md       Thin pointer to the inception role brief + project deltas.
│   ├── orchestrator.md    Thin pointer to the orchestrator role brief + project deltas.
│   └── diagnostic.md      Thin pointer to the diagnostic role brief + project deltas.
└── production-contract.md (only present if a production target was declared at inception)
```

---

## Brain side (orchestrator memory)

```
{{HOME}}/brain/
├── BRAIN.md               Brain identity — domain, entity types, schema pointer, rules.
│                          NOT a CLAUDE.md (avoids auto-loading when cwd is inside brain/).
├── raw/                   Drop-zone for material to ingest (docs, specs, transcripts).
│   └── _extracted/        Cached extracted text from PDFs / binaries.
├── wiki/
│   ├── sources/           One factual summary per ingested document.
│   ├── entities/          Repo "nouns": modules, services, deps, people, tools.
│   ├── concepts/          Architecture patterns, conventions, invariants.
│   ├── decisions/         ADR-style decision records — WHY things are the way they are.
│   ├── index.md           Master catalog of all brain pages.
│   └── log.md             Chronological op record (ingest / page-add / reconcile / lint).
└── .brainmeta.json        Cached metadata (last_ingest, page counts).
```

Brain schema: `~/.claude/skills/gitos/references/brain-schema.md`

The brain is the orchestrator's long-term memory. It is self-contained: every fact it holds
comes from this repo's own docs, code, and decisions — no external service, no shared vault.
The orchestrator reads, queries, and grows it as it works. Agents do not edit the brain
directly during diagnostic-only sessions.
